overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate existing features against a detailed
  specification and identify any gaps. The agent systematically analyzed the
  codebase and then proceeded to implement several critical enhancements. Key
  additions included a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with safety
  warnings, and sophisticated detection logic for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep
  Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, each accompanied by tailored
  recommendations in the generated reports. The agent also integrated a weighted
  scoring system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) and expanded the CSV
  export functionality to encompass all questionnaire data. Furthermore, new
  questions were introduced to screen for pain severity and chronic fatigue,
  with corresponding UI updates and report generation logic for both web and PDF
  formats. The implementation involved meticulous updates across types,
  validation schemas, UI components, and report generation, ensuring a more
  robust and clinically relevant questionnaire.
